  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Flood Response to 150 Families, Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Devastating floods stirred by the outburst of the Shabele River has displaced approximately 11 thousand families in Jowhar, Middle Shabelle region, Somalia, causing one of the worst humanitarian crises in the region. The flooding steadily started early April 2013 but during September spread to dozens of villages in Jowhar mainly inhabited by a predominantly peasant Somali Bantu regarded politically as one of the minor clans in the country. The disaster affected mainly women, children and elderly</narrative>
  </description>
